Troops feel more pity than respect.
The event was a celebration on Wall Street that raised millions of dollars for New York's homeless veterans.
Kid Rock sang a ballad about helplessness and disappointment and loss.
At the signal, several hundred soldiers, sailors, airmen and marines lined up around him.
