Until 2017, the structural deficit of the state budget must be reduced by 0.75% of the gross domestic product (GDP) each year, and from 2017 the structural deficit of the state budget of the federal state in any year must not exceed 0.35% of GDP, and the land, like the municipalities, must present balanced budgets.
The goal is to get the public debt to fall below the 60% mark set by the Maastricht Treaty by 2020/2021.
